Sentencas: Oxidation behavior of porous P434L ferritic stainless steel, used for the fabrication of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFC), is studied under anodic and cathodic atmospheres.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Temperature- and atmosphere-dependence is determined for as-sintered and pre-oxidized stainless steel.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Pre-oxidation reduced the long-term oxidation rate.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For preoxidized samples, the oxidation rate in air exceeds that in humid hydrogen for temperatures above 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of PrOx, LSCF-SDC, and Ni-SDC coatings is also examined.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The coatings do not dramatically impact oxide scale growth.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxidation in C-free and C-containing anodic atmospheres is similar.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Addition of CO2, CH4, and CO to humidified hydrogen to simulate ethanol reformate does not significantly impact oxidation behavior.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cr transpiration in humid air is greatly reduced by the PrOx coating, and a PrCrO3 reaction product is observed throughout the porous structure.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A dense and protective chromiabased scale forms on steel samples during oxidation in all conditions.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A thin silica enriched oxide layer also forms at the metal-scale interface.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In general, the oxidation behavior at 700 degrees C is found to be acceptable.
Titulo: Oxidation of porous stainless steel supports for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
